All in between J‘

12:13.900 --> 12:17.768
We should probably get going
if you want to make Havana by noon.

12:18.029 --> 12:21.521
J‘ No one knows
Just why we 're here J‘

12:21.699 --> 12:23.951
[SIGHS]

12:24.118 --> 12:27.485
Quick, say something nice to me.
It's been a dreadful morning.

12:27.705 --> 12:29.081
Would good news suffice?

12:30.625 --> 12:33.583
You wanted to know
if it ever went on the market?

12:33.795 --> 12:35.376
Is it really for sale?

12:35.588 --> 12:39.331
I take that to mean you'd like me
to move forward with the purchase?

12:39.550 --> 12:41.336
Hmm.

12:42.470 --> 12:44.961
Perhaps this day
can be salvaged after all.

12:45.765 --> 12:51.101
J‘ Ah, ah, ah, ah, ah
Ah, ah, ah J‘J‘

12:58.069 --> 13:01.232
Mrs. Forrester?
Special Agents Keen and Ressler.

13:01.447 --> 13:03.608
We'd like to talk to you
about Frederick Barnes.

13:04.367 --> 13:07.074
He was brilliant, ahead of his time.

13:07.287 --> 13:08.993
He was a rising star at work.

13:09.205 --> 13:11.491
I was never quite sure
why he decided to leave.

13:11.666 --> 13:14.829
Were you aware of any problems
Barnes may have been having at work

13:15.044 --> 13:17.877
or in his personal life?
What personal life?

13:18.089 --> 13:20.876
We worked 16-hour days.
Oh, that's an understatement.

13:21.092 --> 13:23.754
He practically had Anne
living in that lab.

13:23.970 --> 13:27.804
He... Frederick was obsessive.

13:28.016 --> 13:31.725
Every research problem
was like a puzzle that he had to solve.

13:31.936 --> 13:35.724
When did you last speak with him?
Five years ago?

13:35.940 --> 13:40.183
Last I heard, he was taking
a teaching job at Purdue.

13:40.403 --> 13:41.893
Is he in some kind of trouble?

13:42.113 --> 13:43.819
Hey, buddy.
This is our son, Ethan.

13:44.032 --> 13:47.445
Is it okay if I go over to Caleb's?
FORRESTER: Mm-hm.

13:47.702 --> 13:51.365
Uh-uh. Do me a favor. Not right now.
Go upstairs.

13:51.581 --> 13:55.039
I'll be right up, okay, sweetie? Go.
Thank you.

13:58.296 --> 14:00.127
Do you have any contact info
for Barnes?

14:00.340 --> 14:02.422
Even an old phone number could help.

14:02.633 --> 14:05.249
Yeah, I might have something
in the kitchen.

14:13.811 --> 14:16.553
I need to ask you a personal question
aboutyourson.

14:17.982 --> 14:21.725
Does he have Kurz disease?
Yeah.

14:21.944 --> 14:24.651
How did you know that?
Because I saw dozens of corpses

14:24.864 --> 14:27.401
infected with a weaponized variant
of the disease.

14:27.617 --> 14:29.528
Barnes released it on the red line.

14:29.744 --> 14:32.611
He killed 37 people,
including a 9-year-old child.

14:32.830 --> 14:35.367
I have a hard time believing
the coincidence

14:35.541 --> 14:37.623
that your son is infected
with the same disease

14:37.835 --> 14:40.702
your former research partner
is now using to commit murder.

14:40.922 --> 14:42.913
If there's something you're holding back,

14:43.091 --> 14:45.753
now would be a good time
to re-evaluate that decision.

14:48.262 --> 14:51.220
Frederick is Ethan's father.
Does your husband know this?

14:51.391 --> 14:52.972
[m1

14:53.393 --> 14:57.727
It just happened. I thought it was best
for the family to keep the secret.

14:58.731 --> 15:00.767
Does Frederick
know he's Ethan's real father?

15:02.819 --> 15:04.730
Yeah.

15:04.946 --> 15:06.902
When Ethan was 5,
he developed Kurz

15:07.115 --> 15:11.324
and they told us it was untreatable.
Frederick wouldn't accept that.

15:12.954 --> 15:15.821
He had contacts in
the pharmaceutical industry.

15:16.040 --> 15:19.407
He reached out to them to secure
research funding into the disease

15:19.627 --> 15:22.209
but everyone turned him down.
Why?

15:23.798 --> 15:27.711
Kurz is too rare.
Small disease means small profits.

15:27.927 --> 15:31.215
That's why Barnes is killing. He wants to
infect enough people with Kurz

15:31.431 --> 15:33.092
that it gets on the public's radar.
Why?

15:33.307 --> 15:35.218
Because then it can't be ignored
anymore.

15:35.435 --> 15:38.268
The more people that die,
the more attention the disease gets.

15:38.438 --> 15:41.521
And the more profitable it will be
to invest research dollars.

15:41.691 --> 15:43.147
Putting aside
how insane this sounds,

15:43.317 --> 15:46.445
if you're right,
Barnes is just getting started.

15:51.117 --> 15:54.484
[UPBEAT CUBAN MUSIC PLAYING]

16:07.175 --> 16:11.009
[BOTH SPEAKING IN SPANISH]

16:22.064 --> 16:23.270
Mm.

16:27.361 --> 16:32.230
Manny, as always, you look like hell.
Says the devil himself. Come here.

16:32.408 --> 16:33.739
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

16:33.910 --> 16:36.322
So, what brings you to my neck
of the woods, gringo?

16:36.537 --> 16:38.869
Just you, Manny. It's all you.

16:39.832 --> 16:45.372
Let's talk about strontium-90.
Strontium-90? That's what you want.

16:45.588 --> 16:49.456
Because you can't want drugs
or Qassam rockets like anyone else.

16:49.675 --> 16:52.291
A Qassam rocket is a fertilizer-filled
trash can.

16:52.470 --> 16:54.756
I wouldn't fire that eyesore
at my worst enemy.

16:58.267 --> 17:00.883
How much do you need?
12 kilos.

17:01.395 --> 17:06.480
What exactly are you going to do
with 12 kilograms of strontium-90?

17:09.820 --> 17:11.151
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

17:11.405 --> 17:12.440
[SPEAKS SPANISH]

17:12.615 --> 17:14.355
LULI:
I’ve secured the funds on the purchase.

17:14.575 --> 17:17.066
I’m ready to proceed on Red's word.
Good.

17:17.286 --> 17:19.572
I'll let him know
once he's done with Soto.

17:19.789 --> 17:21.700
Excellent.

17:23.584 --> 17:25.120
MANNY:
Six million. I need three weeks.

17:25.336 --> 17:26.997
I need it now.
Not possible.

17:27.213 --> 17:28.419
Fresh out, I'm afraid.

17:28.589 --> 17:32.127
Perhaps I could get in touch with your
previous buyer and make them an offer.

17:32.301 --> 17:36.260
Are you threatening
to cut me out of my business?
We're not that good of friends.

17:36.472 --> 17:40.465
What, are they gonna pull their guns
and hold them all sideways at me?

17:40.685 --> 17:45.304
Manny, I'm sure we can come to
a mutually beneficial arrangement.

17:45.523 --> 17:47.605
I'm listening.
Reach out to your buyer,

17:47.817 --> 17:51.230
convince them to sell back some
of their purchase to you at a premium.

17:51.404 --> 17:52.644
What kind of premium?

17:52.822 --> 17:56.189
My client will put up 10 million
for immediate delivery

17:56.409 --> 17:59.321
with a hefty transaction fee
for yourself, of course.

17:59.537 --> 18:01.027
[m1

18:03.541 --> 18:05.748
[SPEAKING IN SPANISH]

18:14.176 --> 18:16.758
Did he take the bait?
Like a trout to a butterworm.

18:18.264 --> 18:20.129
He Should be calling Barnes
any minute.

18:31.360 --> 18:33.146
[KEYPAD BEEPING]

18:35.573 --> 18:38.064
CaII'S going through now.
Good, run the trace.

18:45.583 --> 18:46.618
[LINE RINGING]

18:47.793 --> 18:48.828
What do you need?

18:49.003 --> 18:50.664
RAYMOND:
A bottle of beer
and a pork sandwich.

18:50.880 --> 18:52.836
How about you? What do you need?

18:53.049 --> 18:54.710
How about Barnes' location?

19:03.976 --> 19:05.011
[ELEVATOR BELL DINGS]

19:05.186 --> 19:07.177
[m1

19:25.247 --> 19:26.703
MAN:
Sir?

19:28.125 --> 19:30.332
Are you with Group 33?

19:31.087 --> 19:32.452
Yes.

19:32.672 --> 19:36.039
I was actually hoping to reschedule
my jury service.

19:36.258 --> 19:39.421
I'll need your summons.
Yes.

19:39.887 --> 19:44.597
TSk. You know what?
I think I left it in my car.
I'll be right back.

19:47.603 --> 19:49.594
[m1

19:55.194 --> 19:56.229
[PHONE RINGS]

19:56.404 --> 19:58.941
Cooper. Where is he?
Red got the 20 on Barnes.

19:59.156 --> 20:02.193
The courthouse in Arlington.
We're on our way in now.

20:15.214 --> 20:16.249
KESSLER:
Federal agents.

20:16.424 --> 20:17.584
Federal agent.
LIZ: FBI.

20:17.800 --> 20:21.008
KESSLER:
Take the north stairwell.
I've got the second floor.

20:21.178 --> 20:23.169
[ALARM BLARING]

20:26.809 --> 20:29.676
All right, everyone.
Single file.

20:36.444 --> 20:38.435
[REMOTE BEEPING]

20:42.283 --> 20:44.865
Your tax dollars at work.

20:45.077 --> 20:46.362
[COUGHING]

20:51.917 --> 20:52.952
MAN 1:
Help.

20:53.127 --> 20:55.960
MAN 2: Somebody help us.
WOMAN: We can't get out!

20:56.172 --> 20:57.878
MAN 3:
Help USI

20:58.132 --> 21:00.168
[ALL COUGHING]

21:10.060 --> 21:12.972
Federal agent, FBI. I'm gonna need
your tanks and your mask.

21:16.984 --> 21:19.396
I need you to evacuate everyone
in this hallway

21:19.612 --> 21:22.649
and get everybody out of here
now, including yourself. Go.

21:31.457 --> 21:33.664
LIZ:
Stop, FBI!

22:01.821 --> 22:03.311
[WOMAN SOBBING]

22:03.531 --> 22:07.399
WOMAN:
Help me, please. Somebody, help.

22:09.662 --> 22:12.404
Hey, it's okay. It'S okay. It's okay.
Stop. Stop. Stop.

22:12.623 --> 22:15.080
We're gonna get help. I've got you.
Come on.

22:17.044 --> 22:19.035
[SOBBING]

22:23.384 --> 22:26.171
MAN: Come on, come on.
LIZ: Out! Out of the way.

22:27.471 --> 22:28.972
Move!

22:35.688 --> 22:36.848
Freeze!

22:37.064 --> 22:38.520
I'm only gonna say this once:

22:38.732 --> 22:39.983
Drop the gun.
BARNES: You first.

22:40.192 --> 22:42.683
If that gun is not on the ground,
I'll Shoot this man.

22:42.862 --> 22:45.899
And you will be dead one second after.
One, two, three.

22:46.115 --> 22:49.073
All right. All right.
Drop the gun and kick it away.

22:49.285 --> 22:52.118
Drop the gun. Now!

22:57.793 --> 22:58.953
Let him go.

23:02.798 --> 23:04.538
[PEOPLE YELLING]

23:35.080 --> 23:37.492
Cindy Wright. You must be Lu.

23:38.959 --> 23:40.369
IS that Short for Louise?

23:40.586 --> 23:43.077
No. Thanks for meeting me
on such short notice.

23:43.297 --> 23:44.332
Oh, not a problem.

23:44.548 --> 23:47.335
As I'm sure my assistant told you,
the house is in escrow.

23:47.509 --> 23:50.000
We're only accepting backup offers.
I understand.

23:50.220 --> 23:53.087
Why don't we head inside?
I'll give you a tour of the property.

23:53.265 --> 23:57.178
Oh, that won't be necessary.
My client's prepared to make an offer.

23:57.394 --> 24:00.557
Double the asking price. In cash.

24:03.484 --> 24:05.816
assuming your escrow falls through,
that is.

24:07.529 --> 24:08.689
[CHUCKLES]

24:12.534 --> 24:16.072
Ijust got off the phone with Dr. Buckner.
She's coordinating triage teams.

24:16.288 --> 24:18.870
How bad?
Twenty-Six confirmed dead

24:19.083 --> 24:21.950
but it looks like the attack
was contained to the jury room.

24:22.127 --> 24:23.913
And your survivor?
Too soon to tell.

24:24.129 --> 24:27.963
But given her level of exposure,
Dr. Buckner'S not optimistic.

24:28.175 --> 24:29.790
What have you got?
MEERA: Casualty lists.

24:29.969 --> 24:32.711
I keep asking myself,
"How is Barnes choosing his targets?"

24:32.888 --> 24:35.755
That got me thinking,
a courthouse and public transportation.

24:35.975 --> 24:39.342
What do these things have in common?
They're both managed by the state.

24:39.520 --> 24:42.011
Right. They both contain
random groupings of people,

24:42.189 --> 24:45.056
various ages, genders, ethnicities.
I'm not sure I follow.

24:45.275 --> 24:48.233
Barnes is targeting large
cross sections of the population.

24:48.445 --> 24:50.982
You don't get a more random sample
than a jury pool.

24:51.198 --> 24:53.905
So Barnes wants to kill different types
of people?

24:54.118 --> 24:56.860
I don't know.
IS it possible these aren't just attacks?

24:57.079 --> 25:00.867
Could Barnes be conducting some
kind of demonstration or experiment?

25:01.083 --> 25:02.823
Agent Keen? A word.

25:14.430 --> 25:15.840
You're on duty, correct?

25:17.099 --> 25:19.010
Are you carrying your badge?
Of course.

25:19.226 --> 25:20.636
Why?
Because it's protocol.

25:20.811 --> 25:23.678
Would you care to explain
why you'd surrender your firearm

25:23.856 --> 25:26.939
to a suspect in the middle
of a hostage Situation?

25:27.568 --> 25:30.526
It was a judgment call.
Barnes was going to kill that officer.

25:30.738 --> 25:34.401
I realize you're new at this, Agent Keen,
but some rules don't have exceptions.

25:34.616 --> 25:37.278
Giving up your weapon,
that happens to be top of the list.

25:37.453 --> 25:39.614
I am fully aware
of our field regulations.

25:39.830 --> 25:42.822
Since you ignored them, your actions
will be subject to a review.

25:43.000 --> 25:45.241
What does that mean?
An administrative panel

25:45.419 --> 25:47.876
will decide whether or not
you'll be sanctioned.

25:48.088 --> 25:50.670
And we'll see where we go from there.

25:58.599 --> 26:00.135
[m1

26:02.686 --> 26:04.267
Mind telling me what that was?

26:04.480 --> 26:07.187
If you're asking whether I reported you,
the answer is yes.

26:07.357 --> 26:08.858
Why would you do that?

26:09.068 --> 26:11.150
Look, Keen. I like you. I respect you.

26:11.320 --> 26:14.812
But back there with Barnes showed me
you're unqualified to be in the field.

26:15.032 --> 26:16.863
You would've taken the Shot,
is that it?

26:17.034 --> 26:19.491
It's easy to make the call
after the fact, isn't it?

26:19.661 --> 26:23.324
It's what any trained field agent would've
done, which is precisely the point.

26:23.499 --> 26:26.741
That hostage would be dead.
Then I guess that's just what happens.

26:27.711 --> 26:29.872
That's a man's life you're talking about.
Yes.

26:30.089 --> 26:32.330
One man's,
which you traded for hundreds,

26:32.549 --> 26:34.835
possibly thousands,
by letting Barnes get away.

26:35.052 --> 26:38.044
And if you can't understand
why that's a bad call,

26:38.263 --> 26:40.128
you don't belong in a tactical unit.

26:45.437 --> 26:47.769
You're a very lucky girl.

26:48.482 --> 26:51.645
Please tell me that's the last one.
The last one, I promise.

26:54.154 --> 26:55.735
What are the tests gonna tell uS?

26:56.865 --> 26:59.322
Whether you have any infection
in your body.

27:01.870 --> 27:04.486
What happened to those people
at the courthouse

27:04.706 --> 27:07.743
is that gonna happen to me?
Not if I can help it, sweetheart.

27:07.918 --> 27:10.204
You just hang tight, okay?

27:19.388 --> 27:21.379
[m1

27:34.361 --> 27:37.478
If you're here for more blood,
I'm pretty tapped.

27:39.324 --> 27:44.444
Nothing that exciting, I'm afraid.
I'm just here to change out your IV bag.

27:57.176 --> 27:58.291
How are you feeling?

27:58.844 --> 28:00.425
[SIGHS]

28:00.804 --> 28:03.295
A little, um...

28:03.515 --> 28:05.426
ththeaded.

28:14.067 --> 28:16.058
[m1

28:25.495 --> 28:27.781
RAYMOND:
Either you accidentally dialed
the wrong number,

28:27.998 --> 28:30.410
or you've hit a dead end.
So which IS it?

28:30.626 --> 28:32.491
Barnes got away
and the trail'S dried up.

28:32.711 --> 28:33.746
[CHUCKLES]

28:33.921 --> 28:36.663
You G-men are top Shelf.
Let me guess.

28:36.882 --> 28:38.418
Ressler slipped on a banana peel?

28:38.592 --> 28:40.878
Know how to find him?
I’m not a gumba/l machine.

28:41.094 --> 28:44.586
You don't get to just twist the handle
whenever you want a treat.

28:51.146 --> 28:53.137
[PHONE RINGING]

28:55.901 --> 28:58.984
We can't keep doing this little waltz.
Don't hang up.

28:59.196 --> 29:00.902
I’m listening.

29:01.782 --> 29:05.320
The reason Barnes is still out there
is because I let him Slip away.

29:05.535 --> 29:07.787
It's only a matter of time
before he kills again.

29:07.955 --> 29:10.492
So, please, [need your help.

29:10.666 --> 29:12.702
Ah. Music to my ears.

29:12.918 --> 29:15.500
What was that last part again?

29:16.338 --> 29:20.251
I need your help.
All you had to do was ask.

29:20.717 --> 29:24.551
I saw in the coverage there was
a survivor from the Arlington attack.

29:24.763 --> 29:26.799
You should assume Barnes
knows that as well.

29:27.015 --> 29:28.175
Which means what?

29:28.392 --> 29:30.804
Has he been to see her yet?
No.

29:31.019 --> 29:33.305
Are you sure?
Why would he?

29:33.522 --> 29:35.888
Barnes may be a scientist
but he's also a killer.

29:36.108 --> 29:41.102
And in that line of work, a survivor
is considered unfinished business.

29:45.575 --> 29:46.701
LIZ:
Maybe we beat him to it.

29:46.910 --> 29:48.992
Or maybe Red was wrong.
What's going on?

29:49.204 --> 29:52.037
We believe MS. Ruben is in danger.
From what? MS. Ruben?

29:52.249 --> 29:55.161
Who's had access to this room?
Dr. Buckner and the nurse.

29:55.377 --> 29:57.459
Lock down the hospital.
No one gets in or out.

29:57.629 --> 30:00.712
I want every Single employee identified.
IS She okay?

30:01.383 --> 30:03.419
BUCKNER:
Help me with her.

30:03.635 --> 30:06.468
What is that?
Looks like a bone marrow biopsy wound.

30:06.680 --> 30:09.296
I didn't authorize this procedure.

30:09.516 --> 30:11.097
[m1

30:11.268 --> 30:15.011
You were right.
They weren't just attacks.
They were experiments.

30:15.230 --> 30:18.142
He was searching for someone
with a natural immunity for Kurz.

30:18.317 --> 30:21.059
You mean like Elysa Ruben?
That's why She survived.

30:21.278 --> 30:24.190
Her test results came back.
She has zero Sign of infection.

30:24.406 --> 30:27.739
MEERA:
So he's going to use this genetic
immunity to synthesize an antidote

30:27.951 --> 30:31.785
then Barnes believes
he has the cure.

30:32.664 --> 30:34.780
He's going for the boy.

30:38.545 --> 30:39.876
[WATER RUNNING]

30:42.716 --> 30:44.547
[DRAIN WHIRRING]

30:46.803 --> 30:48.384
[LINE RINGING]

30:48.555 --> 30:50.466
Come on. Come on.

30:50.682 --> 30:53.264
[WHIRRING STOPS
THEN PHONE RINGING]

30:57.814 --> 30:59.099
Hello?
Mrs. Forrester,

30:59.274 --> 31:00.775
this is Special Agent Keen.

31:00.984 --> 31:04.101
[need you to listen to me careful/y.
Is your son, Ethan, with you?

31:04.321 --> 31:06.528
ANNE:
Yeah. Why? IS something wrong?

31:06.740 --> 31:08.822
LIZ:
Take your son
and get out of your house.

31:08.992 --> 31:11.825
We have reason to believe
that Frederick Barnes is on his way.

31:12.662 --> 31:15.745
[need you to get Ethan
to a safe place. Anne!

31:15.957 --> 31:18.209
Anne, are you there?
What are you doing here?

31:18.418 --> 31:20.534
BARNES: We need to talk.
Mrs. Forrester?

31:20.754 --> 31:24.542
The police are already on their way.
Well, then, I don't have a lot of time.

31:24.758 --> 31:26.714
I need to see Ethan.
It's true, isn't it?

31:26.927 --> 31:30.886
What happened to all those people
on the subway. It was you?

31:32.265 --> 31:35.974
I did what I had to do for our son.

31:36.186 --> 31:38.142
And you'll understand soon enough.

31:38.355 --> 31:40.937
No. Get out of our house.

31:42.025 --> 31:43.936
Anne. Anne.
Stay away from him!

31:44.152 --> 31:46.063
No!

31:46.988 --> 31:48.569
[ETHAN GASPS]

31:49.866 --> 31:51.902
Ethan, don't be scared.

31:52.119 --> 31:54.360
I'm a friend
and I know you haven't been well.

31:54.579 --> 31:58.322
And I'm here to help you.
But I need you to trust me.

31:58.542 --> 32:00.749
Can you do that? Can you trust me?

32:02.796 --> 32:04.787
[m1

32:31.283 --> 32:33.524
Ethan?

32:33.743 --> 32:35.699
No, Ethan. Ethan.
Stop. Stop.

32:35.912 --> 32:37.493
BARNES: Ethan, it's okay. Ethan!
No. No.

32:37.706 --> 32:40.288
Ethan,
I'm not gonna hurt you.

32:40.500 --> 32:43.242
Just relax and breathe.
It's okay.

32:43.420 --> 32:45.411
[BARNES PANTING]

33:06.526 --> 33:07.515
MEERA:
Anne, we're here.

33:07.694 --> 33:09.150
[THUMPING]

33:15.118 --> 33:17.359
Step away from him.

33:18.622 --> 33:21.785
I can't do that. I think you're probably
well aware of that by now.

33:22.000 --> 33:24.116
I know what you think you have
in that needle.

33:24.294 --> 33:26.330
My son's future.
LIZ: Your cure IS experimental.

33:26.505 --> 33:29.167
It could easily kill him.
If I do nothing, he dies.

33:29.382 --> 33:33.500
You don't know that.
Yes, I do. There's no other treatment.

33:35.013 --> 33:38.301
There's no universe in which I let you
stick that thing in his neck.

33:38.475 --> 33:40.966
This is his chance.

33:42.395 --> 33:45.387
This is the only chance
that he'll ever have.

33:46.358 --> 33:48.189
I don't think you're gonna stop me.

33:59.496 --> 34:01.157
LIZ:
Ethan?

34:02.749 --> 34:03.784
Ethan?

34:07.420 --> 34:09.411
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

34:19.516 --> 34:21.507
[HELICOPTER WHIRRING]

34:23.520 --> 34:26.808
LIZ: What are you doing here?
I brought you a souvenir.

34:27.816 --> 34:30.899
What's your feeling about guava?
Anxiety.

34:32.362 --> 34:34.478
Oh, you're in for a treat.

34:34.698 --> 34:38.282
I take it from the coroner's van
that Barnes is no longer with us.

34:44.207 --> 34:45.617
Pity.

34:45.792 --> 34:48.158
Tell that to the families
of the people he murdered.

34:48.378 --> 34:51.461
Every cause has more than one effect.

34:51.673 --> 34:53.334
Say what you will about Frederick,

34:53.550 --> 34:55.836
but someone who's willing
to burn the world down

34:56.052 --> 34:58.509
to protect the one person
they care about,

34:59.222 --> 35:01.133
that's a man I understand.

35:02.142 --> 35:04.724
IS that meant to be directed at me?

35:07.230 --> 35:08.345
Aren't you presumptuous?

35:08.565 --> 35:10.726
IS that how you somehow justify
your actions,

35:10.942 --> 35:13.775
by some misguided
notion of protecting me?

35:13.987 --> 35:15.773
From whom?

35:15.989 --> 35:18.446
My husband, I suppose.

35:18.658 --> 35:20.194
I don't need your protection.

35:22.078 --> 35:23.943
Maybe not.

35:25.707 --> 35:28.414
But I do need you to do this job.

35:29.919 --> 35:32.001
I've accepted that.
And believe it or not,

35:32.213 --> 35:34.169
I appreciate what you do
for the bureau.

35:34.341 --> 35:37.629
And at work, you and I are partners.

35:38.303 --> 35:43.138
But that's where this relationship
needs to end, at work.

35:43.350 --> 35:45.716
I don't want you in my personal life.

35:46.186 --> 35:47.847
I don't know how to make that clear.

35:48.063 --> 35:51.180
You know the problem
with drawing lines in the sand?

35:51.399 --> 35:53.264
With a breath of air, they disappear.

35:54.110 --> 35:55.896
You may not like me.

35:56.863 --> 36:01.277
You may not understand
how or why I do what I do.

36:01.493 --> 36:04.075
But I'm here because you want
answers to questions

36:04.287 --> 36:06.528
you haven't even thought of yet.

36:06.748 --> 36:09.831
Now, if that doesn't matter to you,
the solution is Simple.

36:10.043 --> 36:11.749
I get in this car and I disappear.

36:11.920 --> 36:15.162
You have a deal with the government.
You have a tracking device in your neck.

36:15.382 --> 36:18.795
You don't believe Raymond Reddington
could cease to exist in 60 seconds?

36:18.968 --> 36:21.345
I offer that particular package to clients.

36:22.347 --> 36:23.837
You're offering to walk away?

36:24.057 --> 36:27.766
I'm not going to beg you to allow me
the privilege of helping you.

36:29.020 --> 36:32.057
So say the word and I'm gone.

36:34.484 --> 36:36.315
Tell me to go, Lizzy.

36:36.528 --> 36:38.519
[m1

36:42.033 --> 36:44.445
Then I guess I'll see you tomorrow.

36:52.836 --> 36:54.827
[CAR DEPARTING]

37:02.762 --> 37:06.425
Hard to believe,
but I'm just about finished up here.

37:06.850 --> 37:08.806
Yeah, I'm done.

37:10.019 --> 37:12.226
That was a difficult call
you made with Barnes.

37:12.397 --> 37:14.683
Would've been tough for anyone
in that position.

37:14.858 --> 37:17.099
I keep going over that moment
in my head,

37:17.318 --> 37:20.981
wondering what would've happened
if I'd just let him go through with it.

37:21.197 --> 37:24.280
Given what we know,
that drug was probably the real thing.

37:24.492 --> 37:27.984
What made you do it?
Because you were right.

37:28.204 --> 37:29.614
Barnes needed to be stopped.

37:29.831 --> 37:32.914
If the cure's genuine, it'll be vetted
through the proper channels.

37:33.084 --> 37:35.040
What if it's too late for Ethan by then?

37:35.962 --> 37:38.954
Then I guess that's just what happens.

37:48.683 --> 37:51.925
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

37:53.396 --> 37:54.476
What is this?

37:56.316 --> 37:59.353
We're remodeling.
Clearly.

38:01.279 --> 38:05.522
Long day?
You have no idea.

38:05.742 --> 38:07.698
It's killing you, isn't it?

38:07.869 --> 38:10.702
Heh. Did you really
get rid of all our stuff?

38:11.414 --> 38:15.999
Do you seriously not remember?
What?

38:16.211 --> 38:18.497
Wow, okay. It was Friday night.

38:18.713 --> 38:22.126
We'd just driven in from Rochester
and picked up the keys to this place

38:22.342 --> 38:25.550
but our furniture wasn't coming
until Sunday.

38:25.762 --> 38:28.094
So we drove to the store
and we got Ike.

38:28.306 --> 38:31.173
Oh, yeah, the lamp.

38:32.101 --> 38:34.308
Remember that A was scratched off
the finish?

38:34.479 --> 38:36.891
Poor guy was in the clearance bin.

38:37.106 --> 38:39.097
[m1

38:41.945 --> 38:46.359
And on the way back,
we stopped at that little Chinese place
and got takeout.

38:48.409 --> 38:50.491
That was our first night
in this place.

38:50.703 --> 38:52.659
Yeah.
That's all we had.

38:52.872 --> 38:55.033
It's all we ever needed.

38:57.252 --> 39:00.335
Just you, me and Ike.

